The paper deals with the enumeration of minimal dominating sets in chordal graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithms presented in the paper are based on neighborhood inclusions, which is a technique commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorial optimization (cs.CC). Finally, the paper also discusses the complexity of the irredundant extension problem, which is a topic in algorithms (cs.AL).
